remarks: Well-ordering principle: any nonempty set of positive integers has a least element (schema form).  (Contributed by NM, 17-Aug-2001.)
statement:
nnwos.1 $e |- ( x = y -> ( ph <-> ps ) ) $.
nnwos $p |- ( E. x e. NN ph -> E. x e. NN ( ph /\ A. y e. NN ( ps -> x <_ y ) ) ) $.
$d ph y $.
$d ps x $.
$d x y $.
